SaharaReporters gathered that the incident happened in the Odogunyan area of Ikorodu. A yet-to-be-identified soldier was on Wednesday killed by policemen in Lagos.  SaharaReporters gathered that the incident happened in the Odogunyan area of Ikorodu.  “The soldier was killed at Odogunyan by policemen, he was in mufti. Immediately they realised he was an officer, they ran away to Ogijo police station.  “The soldiers mobilised to the station and burnt a danfo (bus) belonging to the police. There is chaos along Lagos/Sagamu Road. People are rushing home, shops closed," a source told SaharaReporters. 